{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, a substantial portion of the code space remains unexplored.",
    "Therefore, it is important to explore additional states in order to thoroughly test stateful servers.",
    "Unfortunately, accomplishing this task proves challenging for existing stateful fuzzers.In this paper, when the fuzzer becomes unable to explore new coverage, we refer to this scenario as the fuzzer entering a coverage plateau.",
    "Motivated by the study results in Section III-C, we utilize the LLM to assist the fuzzer in surpassing the coverage plateau.",
    "This occurs when the fuzzer is unable to generate interesting seeds within a given time period."
  ]
}